[The apparent attack rate of 17 percent (81 cases out of 485 tested) is
high and suggests that unsafe injection practices were occurring over a
period of time rather than a single time. It is unlikely that 81 patients
received medications from the same vial on the same day. More information
on the findings of the epidemiologic investigation when available would be
appreciated. - Mod.MPP]
